<section id="problem" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-24">
  <div class="section-label mb-4">§1 — The problem</div>
  <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight max-w-3xl">
    AI output is not evidence.
  </h2>

  <div class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl">
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">retrieval without reasoning</div>
      <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
        A vector database returns a ranked list. It cannot explain why each result was ranked where it was, what it did not retrieve, or how its answer would change under a slightly different query.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">generation without provenance</div>
      <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
        A language model produces plausible text. It does not produce a record of which passages it relied on, which inference types were applied, or which facts were asserted without support.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-cardinal-600 mb-2">signatures without binding</div>
      <p class="text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
        A PDF with a digital signature proves only that a file was signed. It does not commit the issuer to a specific reasoning chain, an acknowledged set of gaps, or a survived adversarial challenge.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-14 max-w-3xl text-lg text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
    Under <em class="not-italic text-ink-800">Federal Rules of Evidence 901</em> and the <em class="not-italic text-ink-800">Daubert</em> admissibility framework, expert methodology must be falsifiable, peer-reviewed, of known error rate, and generally accepted. A system whose outputs cannot be independently re-verified by the recipient fails all four prongs. We built Canon because nothing in the field met this bar.
  </p>
</section>
